THE net is closing on people who possess illegal firearms. A 56-year-old woman was arrested after cops found an AK 47 in her house at Machubeni in KwaJongingwenya, KZN. This comes after police embarked on an operation to curb the spread of unlicensed firearms across the province. The operation intended to root out illegal guns and find wanted suspects. It happened on Tuesday.  She was found in the house where cops discovered an AK47 and two firearms. Police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbele said police received a tip-off. She said the cops then proceeded to the house, conducted a search and found the illegal arms. “A total of 52 assortment ammunition were also confiscated. The suspect was charged with possession of a firearm without a license. “She will appear in the Ekombe Periodical Court today,” said Mbele. She said in another operation at KwaMashu Hostel, a 54-year-old man was arrested for possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition. “The Durban K9 unit followed up on information about a suspect in possession of an unlicensed firearm at A section at KwaMashu Hostel. “A search was conducted at the suspect’s premises and a 9mm pistol with three rounds of ammunition was found. “He was then arrested for possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition. He will appear in the Ntuzuma Magistrates Court today,” said Mbele. KZN commissioner Lieutenant-General Khombinkosi Jula said: “The recovery of these firearms and ammunition are evident that we are in each and every corner to eradicate the proliferation of illegal firearms.” Resident Themba Mchunu (29) said a lot of lives will be saved through these operations.